In a statement, the President sends his best wishes to those celebrating the anniversary of the birth of Guru Nanak Dev Ji, the first Sikh Guru. He emphasizes the importance of celebrating the principles of equality, respect, service, and interfaith cooperation that are central to the Sikh faith. The President also acknowledges the contributions Sikh Americans make to the country. He takes a moment to remember the innocent lives lost in the violent attack on the Sikh congregation at the gurdwara in Oak Creek, Wisconsin. The President encourages honoring their memory by recommitting to the spirit of pluralism, equality, and compassion that both the Sikh community and the nation embody.